description:
The "Musee D'Orsay" stop for the "Batobus" (Bus-boat) on the Seine river.

You can go to there to many other Batobus stops on the seine. Easy, quite cheap and refreshing way to visit Paris.

The Batobus is still a Bus (not restaurant, no on board service), but provides some comments. And the refreshing air and view is great. Between Tour Eiffel, the Louvre and the Mus√©e d'Orsay, Notre Dame, the Institut du Monde Arabe, the City Hall, nice visits combination can be done. Plan 45mn to 1h from a point to another (including wait, displacement, hop on, hop off, ticket buying).
